<item>
            <title>[SPARK-10705] Stop converting internal rows to external rows in DataFrame.toJSON</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-10705</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;DataFrame.toJSON&lt;/tt&gt; uses &lt;tt&gt;DataFrame.mapPartitions&lt;/tt&gt;, which converts internal rows to external rows. We can use &lt;tt&gt;queryExecution.toRdd.mapPartitions&lt;/tt&gt; instead for better performance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another issue is that, for UDT values, &lt;tt&gt;serialize&lt;/tt&gt; produces internal types. So currently we must deal with both internal and external types within &lt;tt&gt;toJSON&lt;/tt&gt; (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/8806/files#diff-0f04c36e499d4dcf6931fbd62b3aa012R77&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;), which is pretty weird.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
